description: Supreme Leader Ali Khamenei did not explicitly say an attack would originate from Iran, adding to speculation Tehran plans to retaliate from neighboring Iraq.
title: Iran’s Khamenei warns of ‘crushing’ response to Israeli strikes

description: U.S. officials say they are hyper-focused on any attempts by Russia, China or Iran to exploit the months between Election Day the next president’s inauguration.
title: A chaotic presidential transition could embolden U.S. adversaries

description: Beijing insists it won’t meddle in the U.S. vote, but it’s reaping the fruits of a years-long government effort to build an ecosystem of private hacking groups.
title: China’s Typhoon hacks ahead of U.S. election spurred by elite competition

description: Canadian police said they seized enough drug and chemical precursors to produce 95.5 million potentially lethal doses of fentanyl at the lab in British Columbia.
title: Canada’s largest drug ‘superlab’ in history has been taken down, police say

description: European officials are strategizing how to avoid a trade war, how to “Trump proof” security arrangements and how to deal with Donald Trump diplomatically.
title: How Europe is preparing for a possible second Trump presidency

description: Ayatollah Ali Khamenei pledged a “crushing response” to Israel and the U.S., as the Pentagon said it is sending U.S. ballistic missile defense destroyers and aircraft to the Middle East.
title: Live Briefing: Iran’s supreme leader pledges ‘crushing response’; Pentagon bolsters Middle East presence
